  "description": "BUG-HIGH from backlog: SpeechSynthesis reads emoji aloud as literal names (e.g. 'üòÑ' becomes 'smiling face'), disrupting listening practice. Fix:\n\n1. Create `frontend/src/utils/sanitizeForSpeech.ts` exporting `sanitizeForSpeech(text: string): string` that strips Unicode emoji ranges and decorative symbols before TTS. Use a regex covering: emoticons (U+1F600‚ÄìU+1F64F), misc symbols & pictographs (U+1F300‚ÄìU+1F5FF), transport (U+1F680‚ÄìU+1F6FF), supplemental symbols (U+1F900‚ÄìU+1F9FF), symbols & pictographs ext-A (U+1FA70‚ÄìU+1FAFF), dingbats (U+2700‚ÄìU+27BF), misc symbols (U+2600‚ÄìU+26FF), regional indicators (U+1F1E6‚ÄìU+1F1FF), variation selectors (U+FE0F), zero-width joiner (U+200D), and skin-tone modifiers (U+1F3FB‚ÄìU+1F3FF). Also collapse the resulting extra whitespace and trim. Display text is unaffected (only the speak() argument).\n\n2. Modify `frontend/src/hooks/useSpeechSynthesis.ts`: in `speak()`, call `sanitizeForSpeech(text)` and pass the sanitized string into `new SpeechSynthesisUtterance(...)`. If the sanitized string is empty/whitespace, return early without speaking.\n\n3. Update conversation system prompts in `app/prompts.py` (the conversation-related system prompts used in `app/services/conversation_*` / Copilot calls) to append the instruction: 'Do not include emojis or decorative icons in your reply.' Add this line to each conversation/personality system prompt template so the model stops emitting emoji at the source.\n\n4. Add `frontend/src/utils/sanitizeForSpeech.test.ts` (Vitest) with cases: plain text passes through, single emoji removed ('Hello üòÑ!' ‚Üí 'Hello !'... then trimmed/collapsed to 'Hello!'), flag emoji (regional indicator pair) removed, ZWJ family sequence ('üë®‚Äçüë©‚Äçüëß') removed, skin-tone modifier ('üëãüèΩ') removed, variation selector heart ('‚ù§Ô∏è') removed, all-emoji string returns empty.\n\nThis fixes a WCAG/UX regression where TTS pollutes the listening experience without affecting visual presentation.",
  "files_to_modify": [
